🔍 Model Explanation
K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
The algorithm works on the proximity principle: similar things exist in close proximity.

K = 5 means the model looks at the 5 nearest neighbors

Majority vote determines the predicted class

Distance metric: Euclidean distance (default)

Why KNN?
Simple to understand and implement

No training phase (lazy learning)

Works well for small datasets with clear clusters

